        <h3>Cholecystitis</h3>
        <p>Acute cholecystitis is a condition which is becoming more frequent in our population as major lifestyle changes occur with dietary shifts towards a western diet. This has increased the incidence of cholesterol related illness of which gallstone disease is one. Calculous cholecystitis (gallstone-related cholecystitis) is the commonest indication for cholecystectomy in Zimbabwe. In young patients exclusion of haemolytic anaemia especially sickle cell anaemia is important.</p>
